draw(B--C--A);
draw(B--D--A);
draw(C--D);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$D$", D, NE);
label("$a$", (B + C)/2, NW);
label("$b$", (B + D)/2, E);
label("$2$", (A + C)/2, W);
label("$8$", (A + D)/2, N);
[/asy]

The area of triangle $ABC$ is $\frac{1}{2} \cdot 3 \cdot 2 = 3,$ so the height of the tetrahedron with respect to face $ABC$ is $\frac{2V}{3} = 2.$  The area of triangle $ABD$ is $\frac{1}{2} \cdot 3 \cdot 8 = 12,$ so the height of the tetrahedron with respect to face $ABD$ is $\frac{2V}{3 \cdot 4} = \frac{V}{6}.$  Then
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot 3 \cdot \sqrt{7} \cdot 2 = 3V,\]so $V = \boxed{\frac{2 \sqrt{7}}{7}}.$
